WEBVTT

0
00:00:03.400 --> 00:00:08.130
The open rack wide is no longer just a design specification.

1
00:00:08.949 --> 00:00:14.060
The OCP ecosystem is actively building and deploying this massive

2
00:00:14.060 --> 00:00:17.899
infrastructure to power the next generation of artificial intelligence.

3
00:00:18.430 --> 00:00:18.790
Today,

4
00:00:18.829 --> 00:00:22.670
we are looking at how the industry brings this architecture to life.

5
00:00:23.260 --> 00:00:24.770
To accelerate adoption,

6
00:00:25.090 --> 00:00:28.370
engineering teams develop internal reference solutions

7
00:00:28.370 --> 00:00:30.559
to prove the architecture at scale.

8
00:00:30.799 --> 00:00:34.799
A prime example is the AMD Helios AI rack,

9
00:00:35.090 --> 00:00:39.490
which is built on foundational OCP designs originally contributed.

10
00:00:39.590 --> 00:00:40.470
By Meta

11
00:00:40.639 --> 00:00:41.470
and Ridal,

12
00:00:41.849 --> 00:00:44.529
Helios serves as a highly optimized

13
00:00:44.529 --> 00:00:48.509
reference instantiation of the ORW specification.

14
00:00:48.930 --> 00:00:51.810
By looking at the Helios compute trays,

15
00:00:52.009 --> 00:00:55.889
you can see the true value of the 1200 millimeter width.

16
00:00:56.369 --> 00:01:00.330
The design showcases how larger AI accelerators,

17
00:01:00.599 --> 00:01:03.830
closely and efficiently packed scale-up networking,

18
00:01:04.050 --> 00:01:05.970
expansive memory configuration,

19
00:01:06.050 --> 00:01:08.029
and liquid cooling manifolds

20
00:01:08.209 --> 00:01:12.370
all integrate seamlessly with a single continuous chassis.

21
00:01:13.129 --> 00:01:17.050
But the open hardware ecosystem thrives on adaptation.

22
00:01:17.339 --> 00:01:20.099
Partners take these reference designs and

23
00:01:20.099 --> 00:01:24.000
deliver fully realized turnkey commercial solutions.

24
00:01:24.620 --> 00:01:25.419
For example,

25
00:01:25.580 --> 00:01:28.660
the HPE co-branded Helios deployment

26
00:01:28.860 --> 00:01:36.360
combines 72 AMD instinct GPUs with purpose-built Ethernet scale-out networking

27
00:01:36.540 --> 00:01:38.500
and advanced direct liquid cooling.

28
00:01:38.870 --> 00:01:44.099
And with new ORW implementations from partners like Super Micro being announced,

29
00:01:44.389 --> 00:01:48.489
the market for ORW infrastructure is expanding rapidly.

30
00:01:49.440 --> 00:01:52.870
From reference designs to massive commercial deployments,

31
00:01:53.199 --> 00:01:57.519
the Open Rack Wide is actively reshaping the modern data center.

32
00:01:58.669 --> 00:02:00.300
But AI is moving fast,

33
00:02:00.610 --> 00:02:01.379
and next,

34
00:02:01.720 --> 00:02:04.589
we will explore the extreme megawatt trends

35
00:02:04.589 --> 00:02:07.160
pushing this hardware to its absolute limits.